    <h3>How to use?</h3>
    <p>Include One.js with a script tag at the end of body tag</p>

<% highlight_syntax :html do %>
<body>
  ...
  <script src="one"></script>
</body>
<% end %>

<br>

<h3>Events</h3>

<% highlight_syntax :html do %>
...
<a id="click-me" href="#">Click me!</a>
...
<% end %>

<p><a id="click-me" href="#">Click me!</a></p>

<% highlight_syntax :javascript do %>
$.ready(function() {
  $('#click-me').on('click', function(e) {
    e.preventDefault()
    alert('Thanks for visiting!')
  })
})
<% end %>

<br>

    <h3>Selectors</h3>
    <p>One.js selector wrap "querySelectorAll" to support more features like: Adjacent previous sibling combinator <b><%= highlight_syntax('"-"', :javascript, :tag => 'span') %></b>, General previous sibling combinator <b><%= highlight_syntax('"<~"', :javascript, :tag => 'span') %></b></p>
    
<% highlight_syntax :javascript do %>
//Adjacent previous sibling combinator
$('#container').find('- div')

//General previous sibling combinator
$('#container').find('<~ div')
<% end %>

<br>
  
    <h3>Ajax</h3>
    <p>One.js ajax support full XMLHttpRequest Level 2 and modify a bit to make it more convenient.</p>
    
<% highlight_syntax :javascript do %>
$.ajax('/hello', function(response) {
  // do something
})

$.ajax('/hello', {
  onStart: function(e) {
    // do something
  }
  ,onSuccess: function(response, e) {
    // do something
  }
})

$.getJson('/data.json', function(data) {
  // do something
})
<% end %>

<h3>JSONP</h3>
<p>JSONP is not a part of XMLHttpRequest. So One.js seperate it from ajax.</p>

<% highlight_syntax :javascript do %>
$.getJsonP('http://data.json', function(data) {
  // do something
})
<% end %>

